Here is the "piece" Hilda spoke at the church the other $$$$. night. She had toe have something, and it seems that first $$$$ rate poets have written almost nothing about Christmas-everything by awful dubs and always on the Santa Claus stuff, never on the Christ spirit. Of course, Christmas is a Jew lie grafted on a Pagan superstition and utilized for $$$ profit by the merchants. But I thought it woudl be fun to kid the pious Christ-killers of the church, so I wrote this thing for Hilda. No one knows who wrote it. We said it was "anonymous". 
The Meaning of Christmas
This holiest of all the nights-
I wonder what it means: 
It's surely more than candlelights
On tinselled evergreens! 
It's more than toys that make it dear, 
And eating pleasant things;
For if you listen right, you'll hear 
A murmuring of wings.
My grandma says it's more than fun 
And hanging up your stocking ;
It's knowing any needy one
Might be the savior knocking:
It's helping those who feel the rod 
of grief and heavy labors.
I guess it's being nice to God 
By loving all your neighbors! 
